					<additions><p>F.1r: seal of ʿIbād Allāh (1188). This ownership seal appears in around 15 of Polier's manuscripts in the Pote collection. Other manuscripts containing that seal include: Edinburgh 295 (Yūsuf-u Zalaykhā), Edinburgh 300 (Dīwān-i ʿUrfī) and Edinburgh 317 (Ṭilism-i Ḥayrat) - all works for which Polier had other copies - and perhaps Edinburgh 293 (Kullīyāt-i Jāmī); also BL IO Islamic 1612, a work of Indian travel.</p> 
					</additions>
